<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-31T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="293" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1431/67: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-31T12:00:00-06:00">August 31,
                                1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>55. I have just complied with the Department’s telegram No. 28, August
                            30, 7 p.m., and the Minister for Foreign Affairs told me this Government
                            is prepared to begin negotiations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>